ownedComment.body:
Actors are the users of the system being modeled. Each Actor will have a well-defined role, and in the context of that role have useful interactions with the system.
A person may perform the role of more than one Actor, although they will only assume one role during one use case interaction.
An Actor role may be performed by a non-human system, such as another computer program.

The Use Case model is a catalogue of system functionality described using UML Use Cases. Each Use Case represents a single, repeatable interaction that a user or "actor" experiences when using the system.
A Use Case typically includes one or more "scenarios" which describe the interactions that go on between the Actor and the System, and documents the results and exceptions that occur from the user's perspective.
Use Cases may include other Use Cases as part of a larger pattern of interaction and may also be extended by other use cases to handle exceptional conditions

This package contains use cases which define how an Actor will interact with the proposed system.
Each interaction may be specified using scenarios, sequence diagrams, communication diagrams and other dynamic diagrams or textual descriptions which together describe how the system, when viewed as a "black-box", interacts with a user.
The System Boundary shows the logical interface between users and the system being described.

properties.documentation: Basic Course The system displays the Partner Login page. The user enters a username and password into the username and password text fields respectively and presses the Sign In button. The system validates the username and password combination by querying the system database. The system database returns a match with the username and password combination. The system provides access to the Partner Portal. Alternate Course The system displays the Partner Login page. The user enters a username and password into the username and password textfields respectively and presses the Sign In button. The system validates the username and password combination by querying the system database. The system database does not find a match with the username and password combination. The system displays and error message and returns the user to the Partner Login page. Forgotten Password Course The system displays the Partner Login page. The user clicks on the Forgot my password link. The system prompts the user for their account email address. The user enters their account email address and clicks the Reset Password button. The system queries the database for the account email address. If a match is found a Reset Password Confirmation email is sent to the email address.
